         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Evidently a ¶  ¶ Rafflesia ¶  ¶ allied to R. ¶  ¶ Arnoldi. Only the much smaller R. ¶  ¶ Cumingi ¶ R. cumingii? ¶  ¶ was known before from the ¶  ¶ Phillippines. ¶ Seealso M to L. Keogh, April 1889...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.03.00f</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Gardeners' Chronicle</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Letter not found. The text<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>given<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>here is from ‘A new Rafflesia’,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners’ chronicle</seg>, 4 May 1889, p. 562. The article opens by quoting, unacknowledged, a report in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 5 March 1889, p. 7, concerning the discovery<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in Mindanao, the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Philippines,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of ‘a specimen in full bloom, a five-petalled flower, nearly a yard in diameter — as large as a carriage-wheel, in fact.’ The quotation from M's letter is introduced by '<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Baron von<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Mueller</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">com</seg>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">municating</seg>
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to us this intelligence, says'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The letter is dated to March as the latest date that it could have been sent to have been reported in this issue. It is likely that M sent a cutting from the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, soon after it was published; he may not have included the name of the source newspaper.<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Evidently a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Rafflesia<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>allied to R.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Arnoldi. Only the much smaller R.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Cumingi<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R. cumingii?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was known before from the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Phillippines.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also M to L. Keogh, April 1889</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">in this edition as 89-04-00b</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Rafflesia Arnoldi</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Rafflesia Cumingi</p>
         </div>
